---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/PumpLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "February 12, 2026";
const contactEmail = "hello@asantinos.com";
---

<Layout
    title="Privacy Policy - Pump"
    description="Privacy Policy for Pump app"
>
    <main class="min-h-screen px-6 py-16">
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            <a
                href="/"
                class="text-sm text-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors"
            >
                &larr; Back to Pump
            </a>

            <h1 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
                Privacy Policy
            </h1>

            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
                Last updated: {lastUpdated}
            </p>

            <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-neutral-400">
                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Overview
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump is designed to be simple and privacy-first. We do
                        not collect, sell, or share your personal data. All workout
                        data is processed locally on your device.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        What data Pump accesses
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump can access your workout data from Apple Health
                        (HealthKit) to sync your training activity. This
                        access is optional and only happens if you grant
                        permission.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            Health data accessed: workout data (exercises, duration, calories burned).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Purpose: to sync your training activity with Apple Health.
                        </li>
                        <li>Storage: on-device only.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        What data we collect
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump does not collect any personal data. In
                        particular:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                        <li>No accounts or sign-in.</li>
                        <li>No analytics or tracking identifiers.</li>
                        <li>No advertising SDKs.</li>
                        <li>No location data.</li>
                        <li>No contact information is collected by the app.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Data sharing
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump does not transmit your HealthKit data or any
                        other personal information to external servers. We do
                        not share data with third parties.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Third-party services
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump does not integrate with third-party analytics,
                        advertising, or tracking services.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Your choices and controls
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        You can control Health access at any time in iOS
                        Settings:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            Go to <span class="text-neutral-200">Settings</span> →
                            <span class="text-neutral-200">Health</span> →{" "}
                            <span class="text-neutral-200"
                                >Data Access &amp; Devices</span
                            > → <span class="text-neutral-200">Pump</span>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Disable access to stop Pump from reading
                            Health data.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        Pump does not store your data on servers, so there is
                        nothing to export or delete outside your device.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Children’s privacy
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Pump does not knowingly collect personal information
                        from anyone, including children. The app has no
                        accounts, no social features, and no data collection.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Changes to this policy
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        If Pump’s privacy practices change, this policy will
                        be updated and the “Last updated” date will be revised.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-100">
                        Contact
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you
                        can contact me at{" "}
                        <a
                            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
                            class="text-neutral-200 underline decoration-neutral-700 underline-offset-4 hover:text-neutral-100 hover:decoration-neutral-500 transition-colors"
                        >
                            {contactEmail}
                        </a>
                        .
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
